<P>
CELEBRATING BLACK HISTORY MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Actress Ellaraino, who has appeared in the film "House Party," the TV show 
"Beverly Hills, 90210" and in other films and series, will lead two 
storytelling shows at the annual exhibition of fine art in honor of Black 
History Month. 
</P>
<P>
 The event continues today through Sunday at the Baldwin Hills Crenshaw Plaza, 
3650 W. Martin Luther King Blvd., with storytelling, children's theater, magic 
and juggling, mask-making, and arts and crafts. 
</P>
<P>
 Ellaraino will appear today at 10 a.m. and noon; her topics are "The Black 
West and African American Inventions" and "Ring Games and Story Circles." 
</P>
<P>
 The exhibition coincides with Plaza hours: 10 a.m.-9 p.m. today and Friday, 10 
a.m.-7 p.m. Saturday and 11 a.m.-6 p.m. Sunday. Reservations are needed for 
class workshops during school hours. Admission is free. For schedule of events, 
call (213) 939-0250. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
