<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; ESTANCIA KEEPS COACH BROWN AT 399 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Hills' Dave Brown will have to wait another day to gain his 400th 
coaching victory. Estancia kept him from that milestone Wednesday by defeating 
the Hawks, 60-51, in a Pacific Coast League boys' basketball at Laguna Hills 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Zack Richardson, Clay Frenz and Chris Candlish each scored 15 points for 
Estancia. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Scaglione had 15 points and eight rebounds for the Hawks, who led, 18-14, 
at the end of the first quarter and trailed, 33-31, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown will get another shot at 400 Friday night against Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Pacific Coast League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Century 70, Costa Mesa 48 -- Sixth-ranked Century (20-3, 6-1) remained tied 
for the league lead with Trabuco Hills. Hector Negrete scored 17 and Thomas 
Harmon 15 for the host Centurions. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills 65, Laguna Beach 61 -- Ryan Karnoff scored 19 points, Rob 
Warnick had 18 and John Paisley 16 for the No. 8 Mustangs. Ian McDonald had a 
game-high 29 points and Brandon Bloch had 16 points for Laguna Beach (5-16, 
1-6). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 85, Villa Park 69 -- Erik Williams, who had 17 rebounds, scored 24 of 
his 34 points in the second half for host Foothill (9-14, 3-4). Sean Morris 
added 18 points for the Knights. Villa Park drops to 3-16, 0-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 69, Canyon 40 -- David Neal had 12 points, 10 rebounds and six assists 
and third-ranked Orange (19-2, 7-0) won its 10th consecutive game. Pat Krauss 
had a game-high 14 points and Gil Gonzales had 13 points and eight rebounds for 
the Panthers. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley 91, El Modena 45 -- Olujimi Mann had 27 points and nine 
assists and Michael Riggins had 20 points for fourth-ranked Santa Ana Valley 
(20-3, 6-1). Ryan Villmer and Seijin Lee each had 12 points for El Modena 
(9-13, 3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 46, Cypress 40 -- Esperanza (15-7, 5-2) remained in second place, 
two games behind Los Alamitos after defeating Cypress (12-10, 3-4) at home. 
Mike Thimgan had a game-high 18 points for the Aztecs. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 66, El Dorado 53 -- Katella (13-7, 4-3) took over sole possession of 
third place with a 13-point victory at El Dorado. Mike Pahl had a game-high 17 
points for the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 71, Loara 40 -- The No. 2 Griffins outscored Loara, 25-6, in the 
third quarter. Ali Ton had 17 points and Ryan Staniec had 15 points for Los 
Alamitos (19-3, 7-0). Scott Davis finished with a game-high 18 points for Loara 
(11-11, 1-6). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande 61, Santiago 48 -- Bolsa Grande (11-10, 7-4) remained tied for 
second place with la Quinta after a 13-point victory at home. Tuan Pham led the 
Matadores with 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 69, Garden Grove 60 -- Rich Anderson had a game-high 22 points and 
nine rebounds and Alex Garcia had 12 points, 11 rebounds and eight assists for 
Kennedy (7-15, 5-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Campuzano had 18 points and Tim Denk had 14 for Garden Grove (7-14, 2-9). 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 77, Los Amigos 59 -- Kevin Doane scored 26 points and Greg 
Greenfield scored 24 for La Quinta (12-9, 7-4). Chris Yu and Jason Weiss each 
had 14 points for Los Amigos (10-12, 6-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica 45, Rancho Alamitos 37 -- Jon Surface scored 19 points and Chris 
Vlasic had 12 for fifth-ranked Pacifica (20-1, 11-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 51, Saddleback 44 -- Ramin Bastini, who had six blocked shots, 
had 13 points and Eric Schiff added 10 points for host Corona del Mar (12-11, 
4-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 41, Newport Harbor 39 -- Brad Finneran made a 12-foot jumpshot 
with two seconds remaining for seventh-ranked Santa Margarita (18-5, 10-1). 
Finneran scored 13 of his 26 points in the first quarter. Ramy Shoukry scored 
15 points for host Newport Harbor (11-12, 4-7), which held Santa Margarita to 
19 points in the final three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 75, University 63 -- Five out of six players scored in double figures 
for Tustin (16-7, 9-2). Doug Gottlieb scored 17 points and David Lalazarian 15. 
Demitrius Zeigler had 28 points for University (13-9, 6-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 69, Irvine 54 -- Chris Talbot scored 15 points to lead Woodbridge 
(10-12, 4-7) at home. Greg Foster had a game-high 24 for Irvine (8-15, 3-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's 93, Malibu Camp Kilpatrick 45 -- Damian Raibon had 33 points 
and 14 rebounds to help St. Margaret's win its 11th game in a row. Lupe 
Rodriguez added 16 points, including three three-pointers for St. Margaret's 
(16-3, 6-0). 
</P>
