<TEXT>
<P>
 The Tustin girls' basketball team qualified for the playoffs for the 21st 
consecutive season, clinching a spot with a 57-43 victory over University in a 
Sea View League game Wednesday at Tustin High. 
</P>
<P>
 Sarah Davis had 18 points, 16 rebounds, eight assists and six steals, Erin 
Oakley had 12 points and Alison Carr had three points and 10 rebounds for the 
Tillers (15-8, 7-4 in league). 
</P>
<P>
 Mary Medina and Jennifer Stanley each finished with 12 points for University 
(11-8, 5-6). 
</P>
