<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISTER JOLIE WINS SANTA ANITA FEATURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mister Jolie rallied from next to last to win the $46,000 feature by two 
lengths over Cimply A Winner at Santa Anita Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye, Mister Jolie went five wide into the home 
stretch and drew clear. The 4-year-old Florida-bred gelding covered six 
furlongs in 1:09. He paid $4.20, $3 and $2.40 as the 11-10 favorite in the 
field of seven. 
</P>
<P>
 Prince Wild, the 3-1 second choice, was four lengths back in third. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory, worth $25,300, increased Mister Jolie's career earnings to 
$91,925, with four victories in nine starts. 
</P>
