<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; JEFFERSON'S FREE THROWS HELP SADDLEBACK BEAT 
RIVERSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Antoine Jefferson made four free throws in the final 22 seconds to help 
Saddleback to a 73-68 victory over Riverside and into sole possession of first 
place in an Orange Empire Conference men's basketball game Wednesday in Mission 
Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 Derrick Walsh scored 11 of his 18 points in the second half as Saddleback won 
its seventh consecutive game.Jefferson had a game-high 24 points and 13 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams were tied at 64, when Walsh made a three-pointer from about 23 feet 
with 2 minutes 25 seconds left. Saddleback (18-6, 8-1 in conference) never 
trailed again. 
</P>
<P>
 "I felt it was in," Walsh said. "The rotation was nice." 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside (21-6, 7-2) missed two free throws and Saddleback missed three of 
four over the next 1:30. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside's Raimonds Miglinieks made one of two free throws with 49 seconds 
left to cut the lead to 68-65. 
</P>
<P>
 Tes Whitlock got the rebound, was fouled, and made one of two with 46 seconds 
left. Jefferson made two with 22 seconds left to give Saddleback a 71-65 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside's Brian Dawson made a three-pointer with seven seconds left, but 
Jefferson added two more free throws with five seconds left for the final 
score. 
</P>
<P>
 "It wasn't pretty and I'm not exactly sure why we won," Saddleback Coach Bill 
Brummel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Whitlock made five of 15 shots from the field and finished with 16 points. 
Darryle Flicking had 23 for Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside trailed, 38-31, at the half but rallied and led by as many as four, 
61-57, with 5:30 left. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
