<P>
 Valley College freshman Craig Griffin scored 19 of his 27 points in the second 
half of the Monarchs' 74-66 victory over West L.A. in a Western State 
Conference Southern Division game Wednesday night at West L.A. 
</P>
<P>
 Griffin made all four of his three-point attempts and added six assists.  
</P>
<P>
 Monarch forward Darius Moses had 12 points and 11 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley (10-15, 2-3 in division play) trailed at halftime, 32-30, but scored 44 
points in the second half to pull away. 
</P>
<P>
 In another men's game: 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 69, Bakersfield 56 -- James Parker scored 15 of his 20 points in the 
second half and also had seven rebounds as Glendale posted a WSC Southern 
Division victory at Glendale.  
</P>
<P>
 Mike Wright had 15 points and 10 rebounds and Ryan Asplund added 12 points for 
Glendale (12-12, 3-1). WOMEN 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 52, Ventura 51 -- Blanca Rodriguez knocked the ball loose from Tara 
Sanders to score what turned out to be the game-winning layup with 40 seconds 
left to play, stopping the Pirates' 39-game Western State Conference winning 
streak.  
</P>
<P>
 Both teams are 4-1 in Northern Division play. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez and Edith Bradley led the Condors with 13 points each, while Sanders 
pumped in 21 for Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates were plagued by a 23% (10-42) shooting performance from the floor. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 65, Pierce 57 -- Cicely Brewster had 19 points and seven rebounds to 
lead the Monarchs in a Western State Conference Southern Division game at 
Crespi High.  
</P>
