<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: NORTHRIDGE HOME GAME TO BE PLAYED AT PEPPERDINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge men's basketball game against Northeastern Illinois, 
scheduled for Feb. 10 at 7 p.m. in the Northridge Gym, has been moved to 
Firestone Fieldhouse at Pepperdine, Northridge Athletic Director Bob Hiegert 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Northridge Gym is not expected to be cleared for use until Feb. 14 as 
crews repair damage from the Jan. 17 earthquake and subsequent aftershocks. 
Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 The actual date of Cal State Northridge's home opener remains in limbo because 
of earthquake-related problems. 
</P>
<P>
 Home games scheduled for Feb. 11-12 against UCLA and Cal State San Bernardino 
will either be played on the road or at an alternate site in the Valley, such 
at Pierce College. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge already moved two scheduled home games this weekend to Cal Poly San 
Luis Obispo. Northridge was 12-13 on the road in 1993. Softball 
</P>
<P>
 The Conejo Recreation and Park District is holding registration for its 
spring/summer adult softball league. Applications are available at any district 
facility. Deadline for entry is Monday, and play begins Feb. 22. 
</P>
<P>
 The district also is accepting signups for a 15-hour softball umpires' 
certification course and an adult winter volleyball league to begin Feb. 27.  
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-495-4674. 
</P>
<P>
 The Stealth Premier Traveling Competitive Girls Fast-Pitch Softball 
Organization is holding tryouts at Knapp Ranch Park in West Hills on Sunday 
from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. Tryouts are for two age groups -- 12 and under and 14 and 
under. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-887-4774 or 213-966-3769. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Conejo Valley Adult Education is offering a course in fly fishing on four 
consecutive Saturdays beginning Feb. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 The course covers the basic skills of modern casting, tidal fish behavior, 
aquatic food sources, fly patterns, fly line systems and reading tides and 
beach characteristics. No equipment or experience is required. Registration is 
$24. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-497-2761. 
</P>
<P>
 The Budweiser Fishing Tackle and Outdoor Sports Show is scheduled for Feb. 
11-13 at the Ventura County Fairgrounds. Special events include a fishing 
seminar, a demonstration casting pond, kids' trout pond and a fly-tying 
exhibition. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $5 for adults, $4 for seniors and military, $1 for children 7-12. 
Children under 6 will be admitted free. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-520-1423. 
</P>
