ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Scharp has been appointed chief scientific officer of Neocrin Co., a 
development-stage biomedical company in Irvine. Scharp, an academic surgeon and 
researcher, has taken a leave of absence from Washington University in St. 
Louis to take the position. He will also be a member of Neocrin's scientific 
advisory board. 
</P>
