<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUAKE AID; A RESOURCE GUIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SCHOOLS 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles school board member Mark Slavkin will hold a town hall meeting at 
7 p.m. Wednesday to discuss the recent earthquake, LEARN program and public 
school choice implementation. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will be held at Fairburn Avenue Elementary School, 1403 Fairburn 
Ave., Los Angeles.Information: (213) 625-6387. 
</P>
<P>
 SERVICES 
</P>
<P>
 Westside Center for Independent Living will assist people with disabilities in 
finding emergency services that are accessible and targeted to their needs. 
Information on housing, transportation, mental health and other earthquake 
recovery programs is offered. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 390-6611. 
</P>
<P>
 HOUSING 
</P>
<P>
 Senior citizens left homeless by the earthquake can find free temporary 
housing at five Southern California senior apartment locations and retirement 
facilities operated by ARV Housing Group of Costa Mesa. The offer is good 
through March 1. Seniors will be accommodated on a first-come, first-served 
basis. Information: (800) 624-0236. 
</P>
<P>
 COMMUTER HOT LINE 
</P>
<P>
 Commuter Transportation Services Inc. provides free car-pool matching 
services, road closure and route alternatives, contact numbers for van-pool 
seats and public transit options. Call (800) 286-7433. 
</P>
<P>
 PETS 
</P>
<P>
 The city of Los Angles' Department of Animal Regulation is asking residents to 
turn in lost pets to the nearest animal shelter. Fees have been waived for pets 
that were displaced by the quake. The department, Pet Orphans and Los Angeles 
Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals will assist pet owners who are 
unable to keep their pets at home with free kenneling for two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 To report animals on the streets, call (310) 940-8888. 
</P>
<P>
 * West Los Angeles Shelter (310) 820-2692. 
</P>
<P>
 * Santa Monica (310) 458-8594. 
</P>
<P>
 * Best Friends Hotline (Reunions) (818) 907-4967. 
</P>
<P>
 * LASPCA Kenneling (800) 730-4226. 
</P>
<P>
 Animal Relief fund donations can be sent to: Department of Animal Regulation, 
419 S. Spring St., Room 1400, Los Angeles, 90013. 
</P>
</TEXT>
