<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: HEALTH: FILM, TV FUND OPENS 4TH OUTPATIENT CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Motion Picture & Television Fund has opened an outpatient care center on 
the Westside, the fund's fourth such facility in the Los Angeles area. 
</P>
<P>
 For entertainment industry members and their families, the Westside Health 
Center includes primary care facilities, a pharmacy and a medical lab. 
</P>
<P>
 The center, at 1950 Sawtelle Blvd. between Santa Monica and Olympic 
boulevards, is open Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays from 8:30 a.m. to 5 p.m., 
and Tuesdays and Thursdays from 10 a.m. to 6:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Appointments can be made by calling (310) 996-9355. 
</P>
