<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRAFFIC: APPEAL FOR BEVERLY HILLS TO CHIP IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Now that travel through the Westside has been further complicated by the loss 
of a portion of the Santa Monica Freeway for the next six months or more, it is 
to be hoped that the city of Beverly Hills will do its part by making transit 
easier on Santa Monica and, especially, Olympic boulevards. There is a traffic 
signal at practically every intersection, so poorly timed as to create a 
ridiculous stop-and-go situation even at 3 a.m.! At least between 6 a.m. and 8 
p.m., the lights at minor cross streets should be taken out of service.And at 
other times, if possible, the lights should be set up so that they turn red 
only if a car tries to cross the boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 I know the citizens of Beverly Hills prefer us mere peons going around their 
city, but in circumstances under which everyone in Southern California is being 
asked to make little sacrifices, shouldn't they do their share? 
</P>
<P>
 RICK MITCHELL 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles  
</P>
