<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: FIRMS ELIGIBLE FOR ENVIRONMENT AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Economic Development Assn. is asking business leaders and 
managers to submit entries for its Excellence in Environment Leadership Award, 
an annual honor designed to recognize environmentally sensitive businesses. 
</P>
<P>
 VECEDA, a business lobby and advocacy group, encourages entries from any 
business or organization that works with products or programs to enhance the 
environment. 
</P>
<P>
 The 3M Co. in Camarillo won the award last year after the company 
significantly reduced its toxic air emissions. 
</P>
<P>
 "Winning the award resulted in the kind of positive news coverage that no 
amount of marketing funds could have ever purchased," Jerome Malmquist of 3M 
Co. said in a written statement. 
</P>
<P>
 Entries, which must be submitted by March 1, can focus on compliance with 
regulations on air or water quality, reducing hazardous or other waste, 
recycling, and preserving or restoring the environment. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Kina Batelaan at 642-8137. JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
