<P>
WOMAN, 59, DIES IN CAR ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 59-year-old Simi Valley woman died when the car in which she was riding made 
a left turn in front of another car, police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Yvette Sandra Mohr died of multiple injuries, Deputy Coroner Craig Stevens 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley Traffic Sgt. Jeff Malgren said the accident occurred at 5:38 p.m. 
Tuesday when Eugene James Mohr tried to make a left turn at the intersection of 
Cochran Street and Tracy Avenue in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 His car was broadsided on the passenger's side by a car driven by Carlos 
Morales, 23, who was traveling east on Tracy Avenue. There was no sign that 
alcohol played a factor in the crash, Malgren said. 
</P>
<P>
 Yvette Mohr was taken to Simi Valley Hospital, where she was pronounced dead 
at 6:32 p.m., Stevens said. Her husband was not injured, and Morales complained 
of some pain but was not treated at the hospital. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
