<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBITUARIES ; * FATHER VINCENT J. MCGARVEY; ASSOCIATE PASTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Father Vincent J. McGarvey, associate pastor of St. Thomas Aquinas Catholic 
Church in Ojai, died of a cerebral hemorrhage Wednesday in San Diego. He was 
76. 
</P>
<P>
 McGarvey began to prepare for the priesthood when he was still in high school 
in Philadelphia. He joined the Augustinian Order in 1930 and was ordained a 
priest in 1942. McGarvey served in various parishes for the next 20 years. In 
1962, he was appointed to head the Augustinian Order in the Western United 
States, where he served for six years. During his tenure, the order opened its 
first West Coast seminary in Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Over the next 25 years, McGarvey served as pastor at churches in San Diego, 
Castro Valley and Oregon. In June, 1992, he arrived in Ojai to serve as 
associate pastor. Pastor Patrick Keane said McGarvey was in semi-retirement. 
Parishioners remembered him for his children's Masses, where he asked them to 
sit with him at the altar while he read from the Bible. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was a very gentle, kind man," said Keane, who also remembered McGarvey as 
an avid sports fan. "He always supported the Philadelphia teams, of course." 
</P>
<P>
 McGarvey is survived by three brothers, Thomas, John and Leo. 
</P>
<P>
 A vigil service will be held at 7:30 p.m. Sunday at St. Patrick's Church in 
San Diego. McGarvey will be buried at 10 a.m. Monday at the Augustinian plot at 
Holy Cross Cemetery, San Diego. 
</P>
</TEXT>
