<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: POMONA; COUNTY FAIR WON'T RAISE TICKET PRICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The price of an admission ticket to the Los Angeles County Fair will not 
change this year, fair officials announced recently. 
</P>
<P>
 As with last year's fair, regular adult prices will remain at $8 and children 
6 through 12 will pay $4.Children 5 and younger will be admitted free. However, 
parking for this year's fair, which will be Sept. 9 through Oct. 2, will cost 
$4, $1 more than last year.  
</P>
<P>
 Last year, fair officials cut admission prices to 1991 levels because fair 
attendance and revenues plummeted in 1992 after a 20% increase in admission 
prices. Fair officials said last year's reduced ticket prices helped fair 
attendance reach about 1.4 million -- 162,000 more than in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 From an all-time high of $4.2 million in 1991, the fair association's earnings 
after expenses fell to $850,000 in 1992. Fair attendance dropped from an 
all-time high of 1.6 million in 1991 to 1.2 million in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
