COMMUNITY DIGEST: WALNUT; APPLICATIONS OPEN FOR NEW SENIOR PATROL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Up to 12 senior citizens are being sought for a volunteer uniformed Senior 
Patrol program beginning April 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants must be at least 50 years old and have a valid California driver's 
license, and automobile and health insurance. Those chosen will work at least 
one six- to eight-hour shift weekly. They will patrol city streets in a city 
car marked "Senior Patrol," which will be equipped with a cellular phone for 
reporting graffiti or suspicious activity. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, contact the Walnut sheriff's station. 
