<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PARAMOUNT; SCHOOL BOARD TO BAN SMOKING NEXT YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Students in the Paramount Unified School District have never been allowed to 
smoke on campus, and now the school board is extending the ban to teachers and 
even parents who might want to light up at their kids' ballgames. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustees voted unanimously last week to ban smoking on all district property 
beginning next Jan. 1.Smoking will not be allowed at sporting events or in 
district-owned vehicles. To prepare for the total ban, the board decided to 
restrict smoking to small designated outdoor areas starting March 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Currently, employees can smoke in certain designated rooms, such as teacher 
lounges. 
</P>
<P>
 District health adviser Patti Cummings, who helped draft the proposal, said 
the district will launch an anti-smoking campaign and provide help for staff 
members who want to quit. 
</P>
<P>
 She said the policy is designed to be more educational than punitive, but 
employees who continue to smoke on district grounds could be disciplined by the 
superintendent or school board. "I can't see anyone losing their job for 
smoking," she said. "But leverage can be applied if they neglect the policy. 
Peer pressure will help too." 
</P>
<P>
 The ABC Unified School District in Cerritos and the Los Angeles Unified School 
District have passed similar edicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
