<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MANHATTAN BEACH; MIRA COSTA FOOTBALL CHAMPS TO BE HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A parade honoring the Mira Costa High School football team, winners of a 
Southern Section football title in December, is scheduled for Saturday in 
downtown Manhattan Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants, including the football players, the school band and the drill 
team, will meet near City Hall on Valley Drive at 10 a.m., school officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 From there, they will march south on Valley Drive, then west on Manhattan 
Beach Boulevard to the Manhattan Beach Pier, where a half-hour awards ceremony 
is planned. 
</P>
<P>
 The parade is sponsored by the city, the Manhattan Beach Chamber of Commerce 
and the Downtown Business and Professional Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 798-6460. 
</P>
