<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: INGLEWOOD; CUTBACKS FORCE LIBRARY TO CANCEL SUBSCRIPTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Inglewood Public Library has canceled its subscriptions to dozens of 
newspapers and magazines -- from "Alaska" to "Yoga Journal" -- because of 
recent budget cutbacks. 
</P>
<P>
 Desperate to satisfy the demand for some popular periodicals, library 
officials are asking citizens to help by donating money toward subscriptions. 
</P>
<P>
 The library has developed a wish list of about 60 periodicals. The list is 
available at the main library, 101 W. Manchester Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Miguel Alaniz, the library's director, said canceling the subscriptions should 
save the library about $2,200 in the current fiscal year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
