<P>
 McCaw to Pay Big-Time Bonuses: McCaw Cellular Communications Inc. plans to pay 
$113 million in bonuses to top executives, including $15 million to Chairman 
Craig McCaw. The bonuses will be paid over two years, with the initial payment 
to come when McCaw completes its $12.6-billion merger with American Telephone & 
Telegraph Co., according to a registration statement filed with the Securities 
and Exchange Commission. The merger is expected to be completed by next summer. 
