<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Help-Wanted Ads Rise Across U.S.: The number of ads grew in December in all 
regions of the country but one, an indication that employment is rising, the 
Conference Board reported.The help-wanted advertising index rose three points 
to 110 in December, with its greatest strength in the Mountain, Pacific, Middle 
Atlantic and New England regions, the board said. The year-ago figure was 95. 
The only region that did not experience a rise was the East South-Central area, 
which fell 2.1%. The board surveys help-wanted volume in 51 major newspapers 
each month. 
</P>
