BRIEFLY: TELECOMMUNICATIONS & TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Broadcasters Seek to Enter New Businesses: Television broadcasters have asked 
Congress to allow them to supplement their use of the airwaves with computer 
data and paging services. They said the new offerings would provide competition 
to advanced telecommunications services being planned by the cable and 
telephone industries. In the past, federal regulators have resisted giving 
broadcasters such flexibility. 
</P>
