<TEXT>
<P>
 Court Rejects GM Claims Against VW: The German car maker won a round in its 
feud with General Motors Corp., but the controversial executive at the center 
of the struggle, Jose Ignacio Lopez de Arriortua, is still far from claiming 
victory. A Frankfurt civil court judge rejected claims from GM's Adam Opel 
subsidiary, which had charged that Volkswagen won an unfair competitive 
advantage by hiring seven GM managers after Lopez left GM last March to join 
VW. Lopez remains the focus of extensive investigations stemming from 
allegations of industrial espionage in connection with his move to VW. 
</P>
