<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: SMALL BUSINESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Susan Christian / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Executive Survey: The UC Irvine Graduate School of Management will report the 
results of its ninth annual Orange County Executive Survey at a presentation 
Feb. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Every year, the school interviews 200 randomly selected companies to analyze 
their success rate and optimism.The companies answer questions regarding such 
matters as past and anticipated performance, plans for hiring and satisfaction 
with Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, the biggest surprise was the number of companies considering 
relocation. About 20% of the respondents said they were thinking about leaving 
Orange County, double the previous year's number. 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Aigner, dean of the School of Management, declined to reveal any 
surprises the survey may have this year.  
</P>
<P>
 The breakfast meeting will be held from 7:30 to 10 at the Arnold and Mabel 
Beckman Center, next to the UCI campus. Speakers will include developer Kathryn 
Thompson and Furon Chairman Michael Hagan. Cost is $40. For reservations, call 
(714) 856-5781. 
</P>
</TEXT>
