</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Microsemi Corp.: The Santa Ana custom semiconductor chip company reported a 
profit of $531,000, or 7 cents a share, for its fiscal 1994 first quarter.That 
compares with profit of $1.4 million, or 18 cents a share, for the first 
quarter a year ago, which included a gain of $1.3 million from an accounting 
change. Revenue for the quarter ended Jan. 2 dropped to $26.9 million from 
$30.5 million. Included in the fiscal 1993 first-quarter results was a net loss 
of $234,000 on revenue of $1.6 million attributable to businesses that were 
sold before the start of the 1994 fiscal year. 
</P>
