<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: PACTEL CELLULAR EXPANDS IRVINE HEADQUARTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PacTel Cellular, the Irvine cellular phone maker, has expanded its 
headquarters by signing a five-year lease for an additional 65,132 square feet 
of office space in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 By May, the company will occupy a three-story building at 17900 Von Karman 
Ave. that is owned by Aetna Life and Surety Co.The lease terms were not 
disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Extensive interior rehabilitation of the building is planned, including the 
construction of cellular telephone installation bays and a sales and repair 
center. More than 100 workers will occupy the new building, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
 PacTel currently occupies about 200,000 square feet of office space in the 
Jamboree Center near Main Street and Jamboree Road, also in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 PacTel Cellular, a subsidiary of the PacTel Corp. of Walnut Creek, operates 
cellular and paging ventures worldwide. 
</P>
