<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAMARO IS STOLEN AT GUNPOINT BY 3 MEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three men took a gray 1985 Chevrolet Camaro from a Westminster man at gunpoint 
Tuesday, leaving the vehicle's owner unharmed, a Sheriff's Department spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The car's owner, Benito Ruiz Hernandez, 28, told police that he was approached 
by the three men as he was walking to the car, which was parked in the 8900 
block of Tina Way, about 8 p.m., said Lt. Dan Martini of the Orange County 
Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 When the carjackers demanded his car and keys, Hernandez complied, Martini 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The vehicle, which is still missing, was last seen heading south on Magnolia 
Street, Martini said. The car's license plate number was not released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
