<HEADLINE>
<P>
GETTY TRUST INVITES INTERN APPLICANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The J. Paul Getty Trust is offering summer internships for undergraduate 
students interested in exploring careers in the visual arts and the humanities. 
</P>
<P>
 Students of all cultural backgrounds and academic disciplines are encouraged 
to apply. 
</P>
<P>
 A new aspect of the intern program is a collaboration with the master's 
program in Museum Studies at USC. Interns interested in graduate work in 
curatorial studies and museum education will receive special consideration for 
admission to the Museum Studies program, financial support and the opportunity 
for a graduate internship at the Getty Museum or elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants must be enrolled in, or recently graduated from, an accredited 
college or university. They must have completed at least two semesters or three 
quarters of college at the time of application. Students who graduated from 
college prior to December, 1993, are not eligible. The internships are full 
time, beginning June 20 and ending Aug. 26, and include a stipend of $3,000. 
</P>
<P>
 All application materials must be postmarked by March 7; notifications will be 
made by April 25. To receive an application form, call (310) 451-6545. 
</P>
</TEXT>
